com.github.kaktushose.jda.commands.api

Class ArgumentParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.kaktushose.jda.commands.api.ArgumentParser

  • public class ArgumentParser
extends java.lang.Object
    The default argument parser of this framework.

    This argument parser supports all primitive data types as well as the following JDA entities: Member, User, TextChannel and Role.

    Since:
    1.0.0
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Kaktushose

      • parseArguments

        public java.util.Optional<java.util.List<java.lang.Object>> parseArguments(@Nonnull
                                                                           CommandCallable commandCallable,
                                                                           @Nonnull
                                                                           net.dv8tion.jda.api.events.message.guild.GuildMessageReceivedEvent event,
                                                                           @Nonnull
                                                                           java.util.List<java.lang.String> rawArguments)
        Attempts to parse a List of Strings or respectively the user input in a way to match the parameters of a command.

        Therefore it is attempted to cast each element of the array to the type described by the corresponding Parameter. If the argument parsing fails for one argument and if the Parameter isn't optional, then the argument parsing stops and an empty Optional gets returned.

        Parameters:
        commandCallable - the Command that was mapped
        event - the corresponding GuildMessageReceivedEvent
        rawArguments - the List of Strings to be parsed
        Returns:
        an optional containing a list of all casted objects or an empty optional if the argument parsing failed
        See Also:
        Optional

        guild - the Guild for possible JDA entities
        Returns:
        an Optional describing the parsed argument or an empty Optional if the argument parsing failed

                                                         @Nonnull
                                                         java.lang.String parameter)
        Attempts to cast a String to an object. The object to match is described by its class name and has to have a String constructor. If no constructor is available or the casting fails an empty Optional gets returned
        Parameters:

        parameter - the class name to match
        Returns:

      • formatString

        protected java.lang.String formatString(java.lang.String mention)
        Strips of all characters used in a mention like @, #, &, !, <, > from a String. If the String doesn't represent a mention, it gets returned without being manipulated.
        Parameters:
        mention - The String to be stripped of mention characters
        Returns:
        The String with all mention characters removed
